cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks to extract facial attributes and investigate correlations between these features and attractiveness. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper uses big data and statistical significance tests, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a generative adversarial network (GAN) to enhance beauty in facial images could also place the paper in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
